mention.text: President Richard M. Nixon , who ultimately resigned
Deep Throat '' -- the nickname for the anonymous source who helped guide The Washington Post 's Pulitzer Prize-winning investigation into the Watergate scandal
Watergate 's Deep Throat , '' published after the Vanity Fair article appeared
Deep Throat , a name borrowed from a notorious pornographic movie of the era
a Navy lieutenant assigned to the Pentagon as a watch officer
a cub reporter at the Montgomery County Sentinel , a suburban Maryland newspaper , and later at The Post

Bob Woodward , who with Carl Bernstein made up The Post 's investigative duo who doggedly pursued the story of the Watergate break-in and a conspiracy that led directly to President Richard M. Nixon , who ultimately resigned
Felt 's name a secret , but in 2005 , at the age of 91 , Felt told Vanity Fair magazine
the guy they used to call Deep Throat
a Vanity Fair article by his family 's lawyer
a key lawyer in the Watergate prosecution team
C. Wallace , the Alabama governor then running for president
the Alabama governor then running for president
the legendary founding director J. Edgar Hoover
